library(tidyverse)

  mutate(gender = as_factor(gender))

summary(mall_customers)

Clustering process on spending score and annual income

target <- mall_customers %>% 
  select(annual_income_k, spending_score_1_100)
target %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(annual_income_k, spending_score_1_100), 
               names_to = "type", 
               values_to = "value") %>% 
  group_by(type)%>%
  summarise(mean = round(mean(value)), 
            sd = sd(value))
target_scale <- target %>%
  as_tibble() %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(annual_income_k, spending_score_1_100), 
               names_to = "type", 
               values_to = "value") %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, scale)
# using broom package
max_k <- 20 

k_clusters <- tibble(k = 1:max_k) %>%
  mutate(
    kclust = map(k, ~ kmeans(target, .x, nstart = 25)), 
    tidied = map(kclust, tidy),
    glanced = map(kclust, glance),
    augmented = map(kclust, augment, target)
  )

k_clusters
clusterings <- k_clusters %>%
  unnest(glanced)

clusterings
ggplot(clusterings, aes(x = k, y= tot.withinss)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 25, by = 1))

# library cluster

cluster_list_k5 <- clusterings %>% 
  unnest(augmented) %>%
  filter(k == 5) %>%
  select(.cluster) %>%
  pull()

sil <- silhouette(as.numeric(cluster_list_k5), 
                  dist(target_scale))
NAs introduced by coercionError in silhouette.default(as.numeric(cluster_list_k5), dist(target_scale)) : 
  clustering 'x' and dissimilarity 'dist' are incompatible
clusterings %>% 
  unnest(cols = c(augmented)) %>%
  filter(k == 5) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = annual_income_k, y = spending_score_1_100, colour = .cluster, label = .cluster)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = .cluster)) +
  geom_text(hjust = 0, vjust = - 0.5, size = 3)

clusterings %>% 
  unnest(augmented) %>%
  filter(k == 5) %>%
  group_by(.cluster) %>%
  summarise(mean(annual_income_k), mean(spending_score_1_100))
